reviews.review_text: No Trick Here, Only Treats This is one of those Matrix sources that really keeps the best of both alive and in the combination creates an amazing union.  The show is typical Fall 79 greatness, now the sound has even improved.  How lucky are we?  Keep up the great work, it is most definitely appreciated.

this is betta I reviewed the first half of the show on another source. It was good, but I like this mix. The crowd brings it to life. The high end is more distinct as well. Bumping four to five on the virtue of this being a better sound. Also, the estimated to eys transition is silly good... I mean you are wasting your time with may 77 dude, this is some ripe shit I tell you.

Amazing Second Set. Jerry Switches to Wolf? And really fine recording and transfer. Kudos to the purveyor. This is my "find" of the month. This is a truly hot and well-played show from start to finish, but a huge nod goes to the playing and sonic coverage of the second set which is downright provocative in its scale and tone. All the jams and solos are unique and inventive. 

I don't know for sure, of course, but it sounds to me as if Jerry switched from his Tiger, which he had been using since August, and donned his Wolf guitar for the second set -- maybe it was in order to conjure the rock goblins on Halloween or some such hackneyed malarkey. Nonetheless, the entire second set is molten brimstone.

For example, rarely have I heard a JBG played with such abandon and it surely is a shot in the arm.

One of my favorite shows of the year, so far.

Tasty, tasty morsel. The show and the matrix are both beyond fabulous.  But the Shakedown and the Passenger are beyond white friggin' hot.  If you want to stop by for only a couple songs before you blaze off to work or whatever---try these two.

Halloween, after all Halloween, after all; many people in costume; many people tripping. China Cat to start - wow! People flooding to the front where it was just madness. Calls to move back were to no avail. Finally, they had to play the then unknown Althea Sailor Saint just to calm the crowd down a bit. Second set pretty non-stop though.
Good show. Festive atmosphere. Hilariously unfunny jokes by Weir.
Amazing! I think this show is one of the best Dead shows ever. It's definitly my favorite Estimated/Eyes ever!

Only got a few songs in...and had to comment WOW. Kudos to the work done with this recording. Coming through my Marantz receiver, into my Bose speakers, through the ears into the brain..... I love the late Fall into early Winter of 1979 shows,I cannot wait to get back to the music, and I will be looking for more of this sound engineer's matrix recordings. WELL DONE!

second set fire really excellent Ramble On Rose, top 3 for me
whole second set is fire. great Shakedown
